<h1>Problem 1523 - 2018 AMO, P8 of 8</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Amy has a number of rocks such that the mass of each rock, in kilograms, is a positive integer. The sum of the masses of the rocks is \(2018\) kilograms. Amy realises that it is impossible to divide the rocks into two piles of \(1009\) kilograms.</p>
<p>What is the maximum possible number of rocks that Amy could have?</p>
<h2>Idea</h2>
<p>Prefix-sum PHP.</p>
